Seven persons including the Village Head of Tudun Doki in Gwadabawa council, Alhaji Hayatu Ardo have died in a road crash along Gwadabawa-Illela Road in Sokoto State. Mr Garaba Kanya, spokesman of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Sokoto Sector Command, told newsmen on Wednesday that the crash occurred on Monday night. Kanya said the crash involved a commercial Toyota Avensis car conveying 11 persons which skidded off the road and hit a tree as the driver lost control. He said others who sustained injuries were hospitalised at Gwadabawa General Hospital. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) gathered that the sole administrator of Gwadabawa council, Alhaji Aminu Aya, has commiserated with the families of the deceased.